    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Three new cave-dwelling Eukoenenia (Palpigradi: Eukoeneniidae) from limestone caves in Northern Minas Gerais state, Brazil" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933490>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933488>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933492>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933494>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933496>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933498>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933500>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933502> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933490>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Eukoenenia lundi sp. nov., female holotype. A, propeltidial chaetotaxy; B, metapeltidial setae; C, coxa of left pedipalp; D, coxa of left leg I; E, coxa of right leg II; F, coxa of right leg III; G, coxa of right leg IV. The thickened setae on coxae II, III and IV are indicated by arrows. Scale bars: 100 μm (Fig. A), 40 μm (Fig. B) and 60 μm (Figs. C–G)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3933490/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933488>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Eukoenenia lundi sp. nov., female holotype. A, blades on lateral organ; B, deutotritosternal setae; C, proximal setae (p1–p6) on basal segment of chelicera; D, distal setae (d1–d3) on basal segment of chelicera. Scale bars 20 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3933488/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933492>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Eukoenenia lundi sp. nov., pedipalp, female holotype. A, trochanter, left side; B, femur and tibia, left side; C, basitarsus 1–tarsus 1, right side; D, tarsi 2 and 3, right side. Scale bars 80 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3933492/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933494>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Eukoenenia lundi sp. nov., leg I, left side, female holotype.A, trochanter; B, femur and patella; C, tibia-basitarsus 2; D, basitarsus 3–tarsus 2. Scale bars 80 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3933494/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933496>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Eukoenenia lundi sp. nov. A, leg I, tarsus 3, left side, holotype (scale bar 80 μm); B, leg IV, basitarsus, right side, holotype (scale bar 60 μm); C, first lobe, female genitalia (scale bar 40 μm); D, second lobe, female genitalia (scale bar 40 μm); E, first lobe, male genitalia, left half (the sternal setae inserted close to the lobe are not shown) (scale bar 30 μm); F, second and third lobes, male genitalia, left half (scale bar 30 μm). Dotted circles and ellipses in Figs. C and D represent cuticular orifices; empty circles in Figs. E and F represent insertions of detached setae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3933496/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933498>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Eukoenenia lundi sp. nov. A, chaetotaxy of opisthosomal tergite III, male paratype; B, chaetotaxy of opisthosomal sternite V, male paratype; C, chaetotaxy of opisthosomal sternite IV, female holotype. Scale bars 20 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3933498/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933500>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Eukoenenia lundi sp. nov., flagellar articles, male paratype. A, articles I–VII; B, articles VII–XI; C, articles XI–XIV. Scale bars 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3933500/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3933502>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. Eukoenenia lundi sp. nov. A, Lapa Sem Fim cave, type locality of the new species, plan view; blue arrows point cave entrances (larger arrow indicates the main entrance); collecting site highlighted in red; B, main entrance of Lapa Sem Fim; C, inner portion of Lapa Sem Fim, close to the collecting site; D, live specimen in Lapa Sem Fim. Photos: Lucas M. Rabelo (D) and Rodrigo L. Ferreira." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3933502/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

